                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=rquadling",
                        "name": "rquadling",
                        "displayName": "Richard Quadling",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "I'm wondering if the method should be called normaliseFile() (or normalizeFile() depending upon consensus).\r\n\r\nWith the various ongoing discussions on autoloading functions in the PHP Internals mailing list, a normalize method could be used for all things being autoloaded (interfaces, traits, classes and potentially functions, as well as libraries as I've demonstrated here).\r\n\r\n",
